CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 7, 1945, pg. 13, reads: "'The Younger Set' - Not to be outdone by their elders, Master Alan Isbell and Miss Jacqueline Atkins almost stole the show on Easter Sunday. Shakespeare's line about a young man's fancy could apply here, no? - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Alan Isbell wearing double breasted coat, and Jacqueline Atkins wearing bonnet, posed on sidewalk in front of housing project
